WEBVTT

00:02.000 --> 00:04.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: But first: to
a part of the Trump agenda
that the administration still

00:04.066 --> 00:09.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
has not been able to implement:
his travel ban on visitors from
six mostly Muslim countries.

00:11.066 --> 00:15.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
The revised version of the
ban remains on hold by federal
court order, and the president

00:15.333 --> 00:18.533 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
this morning aired out
his grievances once again.

00:18.533 --> 00:20.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
John Yang reports.

00:20.500 --> 00:24.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: This afternoon,
the White House deputy press
secretary said it didn't matter

00:26.300 --> 00:28.333 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
what President Trump's executive
order on immigration is called.

00:28.333 --> 00:30.333 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
SARAH HUCKABEE SANDERS, Deputy
White House Press Secretary:
I think that the president

00:30.333 --> 00:32.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
isn't concerned with
what you call it.

00:32.333 --> 00:35.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
He's concerned with national
security and protecting
people in this country.

00:35.966 --> 00:40.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN YANG: This morning, the
president was very concerned,
stating: "People, the lawyers

00:42.900 --> 00:46.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
and the courts can call it
whatever they want, but I am
calling it what we need and what

00:46.433 --> 00:48.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
