00:48.900 --> 00:52.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
In fact, it his own aides
who refused to call it that.

00:52.166 --> 00:54.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
SEAN SPICER, White
House Press Secretary:
It's not a travel ban.

00:54.233 --> 00:57.066 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
It's a -- it's a vetting
system to keep America safe.

00:57.066 --> 00:59.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's it, plain and simple.

00:59.133 --> 00:59.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JOHN KELLY, U.S. Homeland
Security Secretary: It's
not a travel ban, remember.

00:59.966 --> 01:02.066 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's a travel pause.

01:02.066 --> 01:05.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
What the president said, for
90 days, we were going to pause
in terms of people from those

01:07.466 --> 01:11.200 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
countries coming to the United
States that would give me time
to look at additional vetting.

01:13.233 --> 01:16.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JOHN YANG: Mr. Trump
also slammed his own
Justice Department,
saying it should have

01:16.666 --> 01:21.666 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
stuck with the original
executive order, "not
the watered-down,
politically correct current

01:23.600 --> 01:26.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
version," even though it was the
president himself who revoked
the original version when

01:26.833 --> 01:29.366 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
he signed the new one.

01:29.366 --> 01:33.533 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
Mr. Trump has asked the
Justice Department to
seek a quick Supreme
Court hearing to reinstate

01:34.966 --> 01:36.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
the order after lower courts
blocked it from taking effect.

01:36.566 --> 01:40.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
It's up to the
justices to decide how
quickly they will act.

01:40.633 --> 01:43.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
For the "PBS NewsHour,"
I'm John Yang.

01:43.233 --> 01:48.233 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Separately,
there's word tonight
that the FBI has arrested
a federal contract

01:50.200 --> 01:53.366 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
employee on charges of
leaking a secret document
on Russian election hacking.

01:55.433 --> 01:58.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
NBC News reports that a
Georgia woman allegedly
gave the National
Security Agency document

02:00.200 --> 02:02.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
to "The Intercept,"
an online magazine.

02:02.666 --> 02:07.266 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
It says it shows Russian
military intelligence
engineered a cyber-attack
on at least one

02:08.733 --> 02:12.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
U.S. supplier of voting
software last year.

02:12.233 --> 02:17.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Hackers also tried to dupe
elections officials into
handing over log-in credentials.

02:19.300 --> 02:22.800 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
It's the first evidence
that Moscow tried to go
beyond swaying public
opinion and interfere

02:23.533 --> 02:25.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
in election machinery.

02:25.566 --> 02:30.100 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
For more on all this and more,
we turn to Politics Monday
with Amy Walter of The Cook

02:30.100 --> 02:33.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Political Report and
Tamara Keith of NPR.

02:33.200 --> 02:37.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, Amy and Tam, this is a story
that has just been breaking
literally within the last

02:37.600 --> 02:39.600 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
hour.

02:39.600 --> 02:43.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
We learned about this online
magazine, Amy, a few hours ago,
but now we're learning about

02:44.666 --> 02:47.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
the arrest.

02:47.300 --> 02:51.033 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
If it is the case that
the Russians were able to
in some way interfere or
get close to interfering

02:53.000 --> 02:55.133 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
